## VIDEO MANAGER – metadata

# Usage:
# ------
video metadata [files] [--key VALUE ...] [--list-tags] [--list-tag-KEY] [--list-tags-json]

# Description:
# ------------
Display, edit, or remove metadata from video files.
Supports both CLI flags and a full-screen interactive menu.
Also checks for and optionally embeds cover thumbnails.

# Main Flags:
# -----------
--list-tags           Show all metadata tags currently set
--list-tags-json      Output all tags in JSON format
--list-tag-<key>      Show the value of a specific tag (e.g. --list-tag-title)

# Editable Tags:
# --------------
--title               Video title
--artist              Creator or performer
--album               Album name
--genre               Genre (e.g. Drama, Sci-Fi)
--comment             Personal comment or note
--date                Release date
--track               Track number in album or series
--composer            Composer of the content
--publisher           Publisher or distributor
--language            Language of the content
--show                Name of a TV show or series
--season_number       Season number
--episode_id          Episode or part number
--network             Broadcasting network
--director            Director of the video
--production_year     Year the content was produced
--keywords            Searchable keywords

# Thumbnail Support:
# ------------------
- Program detects presence of thumbnails (MP4: attached_pic / MKV: mjpeg or attachment)
- Interactive mode allows setting a thumbnail from image or frame
- Existing thumbnails are automatically removed before replacing

# Protected Tags (Not Editable):
# ------------------------------
major_brand, minor_version, compatible_brands, encoder, duration
These are essential for format compatibility and are not user-editable.

# Interactive Mode:
# -----------------
If no metadata flags are passed, an interactive editor will launch:
- Shows all editable tags, grouped by whether they are set or not
- Colored display and aligned formatting for clarity
- Set a tag by entering a value, delete it by leaving input blank

# Examples:
# ---------
video metadata movie.mp4 --title "My Title" --artist "Jane Doe"
video metadata series.mkv --list-tag-director
video metadata anime.mp4 --list-tags-json
video metadata oldmovie.mp4  ← (opens interactive menu)

# Notes:
# ------
- Changes are written directly into the original file.
- It's recommended to back up your files before batch editing.
- Only tags supported by the container format (e.g. MP4/MKV) will be preserved.
- VLC or media libraries may cache thumbnails: use a different filename or clear cache to update view!!!
